01:25:11.141 --> 01:25:12.741
They were just prostitutes.

01:25:12.841 --> 01:25:14.641
Where'd you take them?

01:25:16.541 --> 01:25:19.941
I don't remember junk like that.
You'll have to ask Dick.

01:25:21.741 --> 01:25:23.941
What did these girls look like?

01:25:24.441 --> 01:25:25.941
Describe them.

01:25:26.441 --> 01:25:28.541
Blonde? Dark? Big? Little?

01:25:28.741 --> 01:25:30.041
Any scars?

01:25:30.941 --> 01:25:33.141
Moles? Marks?

01:25:35.641 --> 01:25:37.640
Would you like the sordid details?

01:25:37.740 --> 01:25:39.040
Anything.

01:25:41.740 --> 01:25:44.040
Is that how you get your kicks?

01:25:44.740 --> 01:25:47.140
She had to be a contortionist.

01:25:48.140 --> 01:25:50.740
I guess you know why we're really here?

01:25:51.440 --> 01:25:55.540
You know we wouldn't have come this far
just to arrest two-bit check chiselers.

01:25:55.640 --> 01:25:57.040
Would we, Dick?

01:25:57.240 --> 01:25:59.940
- I wasn't listening.
- Are you listening now?

01:26:00.040 --> 01:26:02.740
Did you ever hear
of the Clutter murder case?

01:26:03.640 --> 01:26:06.040
Can't nobody pin any murder on me.
No, sir.

01:26:06.140 --> 01:26:10.540
- The question was: Did you hear about it?
- Read something about it, maybe.

01:26:10.740 --> 01:26:12.340
You made three mistakes.

01:26:12.540 --> 01:26:14.840
Number one: You left a witness.

01:26:15.140 --> 01:26:18.040
A living witness, who'll testify in court.

01:26:18.140 --> 01:26:20.340
There ain't any living witness. Can't be.

01:26:20.440 --> 01:26:22.440
Nobody can pin any murder on me.

01:26:22.639 --> 01:26:25.139
Saturday, November 14,
you drove to Fort Scott.

01:26:25.139 --> 01:26:28.239
You went to the post office
to get the address of Perry's sister.

01:26:28.339 --> 01:26:29.339
That's right.

01:26:36.539 --> 01:26:39.939
Perry Smith has no sister in Fort Scott.
Never has had.

01:26:40.839 --> 01:26:45.639
On Saturday afternoon the post office
in Fort Scott is always closed.

01:26:46.139 --> 01:26:49.339
That is your second mistake.

01:26:51.739 --> 01:26:53.939
Perry seems confused about that night.

01:26:54.039 --> 01:26:56.439
I think it's about time
we straightened him out.

01:26:56.639 --> 01:26:58.939
Yes, sir. About time.

01:26:59.439 --> 01:27:01.039
Look at me, boy.

01:27:04.839 --> 01:27:09.138
On Saturday night, November 14,
you were in Holcomb, Kansas.

01:27:10.738 --> 01:27:13.338
You were killing the Clutter family.

01:27:14.838 --> 01:27:15.938
Never.

01:27:16.938 --> 01:27:18.738
- I never...
- Never what?

01:27:20.037 --> 01:27:22.837
I never knew anybody by that name...

01:27:23.637 --> 01:27:26.537
...Clutter.
- We've got a living witness.

01:27:38.437 --> 01:27:40.037
Well, Perry?

01:27:42.437 --> 01:27:44.337
Do you have any aspirin?

01:27:45.037 --> 01:27:46.537
They took my aspirin away.

01:27:46.737 --> 01:27:48.137
Feeling bad?

01:27:50.037 --> 01:27:51.437
My legs do.

01:27:57.136 --> 01:27:59.736
By the way, you know what tomorrow is?

01:28:00.936 --> 01:28:02.936
Nancy Clutter's birthday.

01:28:03.436 --> 01:28:04.836
She would have been 17.

01:28:09.536 --> 01:28:11.636
You guys have gotta be stalling.

01:28:12.036 --> 01:28:15.536
If you had any real proof...
Real proof, as in eyewitness.

01:28:16.236 --> 01:28:17.736
Fingerprints.

01:28:22.136 --> 01:28:25.236
As God is my witness,
may I burn in hell forever...

01:28:25.336 --> 01:28:26.836
...if I ever killed anybody.

01:28:26.936 --> 01:28:28.436
Careful, boy.

01:28:33.436 --> 01:28:34.936
Got an aspirin?

01:28:39.236 --> 01:28:40.734
How's it going?

01:28:41.034 --> 01:28:43.134
Three hours and all we've got so far is:

01:28:43.234 --> 01:28:45.734
"No. I don't remember. Ask Dick."

01:28:46.534 --> 01:28:50.834
We've caught that hard-nosed little punk
in 50 lies and he still admits nothing.

01:28:59.134 --> 01:29:01.834
I think our boy's about primed and ready.

01:29:02.734 --> 01:29:04.534
I hope you're right.

01:29:12.234 --> 01:29:14.634
Why do all you people get tattooed?

01:29:17.234 --> 01:29:18.534
"All you people"?

01:29:20.134 --> 01:29:23.434
- What people?
- Convicts. You're all tattooed.

01:29:23.934 --> 01:29:27.833
That tiger head. What does it do?
Make you feel tough?

01:29:32.433 --> 01:29:36.933
That cop's badge, what does it do?
Make you feel honest?

01:29:37.933 --> 01:29:39.733
Everybody's got a tattoo.

01:29:39.833 --> 01:29:41.933
Only you people call them clubs.

01:29:42.233 --> 01:29:47.033
Elks, Masons, Boy Scouts. Salute.
High sign. Low sign.

01:29:47.233 --> 01:29:50.933
Secret this and secret that.
"No trespassing. Keep off the grass."

01:29:51.233 --> 01:29:53.633
Nice, respectable, tattoo clubs.

01:29:54.133 --> 01:29:58.033
Poker clubs, golf clubs, tennis clubs.

01:29:58.033 --> 01:30:00.832
Clubs for gambling and clubs for drinking.

01:30:01.432 --> 01:30:04.432
Even a real club like Daddy-O's got
in that little brown bag.

01:30:04.432 --> 01:30:07.532
What you gonna do, pappy?
Club it out of me?

01:30:08.832 --> 01:30:10.432
Something like that.

01:30:10.532 --> 01:30:12.831
I said you made three mistakes.

01:30:13.231 --> 01:30:15.631
First, you left a living witness.

01:30:16.131 --> 01:30:18.431
Second, your alibi won't hold water.

01:30:18.531 --> 01:30:19.831
And third?

01:30:20.731 --> 01:30:22.031
Coming up.

01:30:24.431 --> 01:30:25.831
Footprints.

01:30:27.731 --> 01:30:30.831
Made in the spot
where Mr. Clutter was murdered.

01:30:33.031 --> 01:30:35.531
These are the shoes that made them.

01:30:38.031 --> 01:30:39.231
Yours.

01:30:42.431 --> 01:30:43.731
This footprint...

01:30:45.331 --> 01:30:47.631
...was made in Mr. Clutter's blood.

01:30:48.931 --> 01:30:50.331
Perry's shoe.

01:30:50.931 --> 01:30:54.531
Same cat's paw. Same size. Same blood.

01:31:02.830 --> 01:31:05.430
All right, Dick. This time the truth.

01:31:10.630 --> 01:31:13.430
I don't want to be charged
with murder one...

01:31:14.430 --> 01:31:16.530
...because I never pulled the trigger.

01:31:17.130 --> 01:31:20.230
I don't even know
what the goddamn hell was happening.

01:31:21.530 --> 01:31:24.130
It was Perry. He did it.

01:31:26.730 --> 01:31:28.430
I couldn't stop him.

01:31:30.730 --> 01:31:32.530
He killed them all.

01:31:54.929 --> 01:31:57.029
Are you the officer that made the arrest?

01:31:57.129 --> 01:31:59.429
If you'd grabbed them
five minutes earlier...

01:31:59.529 --> 01:32:01.929
...before they'd picked up that box...

01:32:02.229 --> 01:32:04.029
Just luck, I guess.

01:32:04.229 --> 01:32:05.229
Or something.

01:32:20.429 --> 01:32:22.829
Hickock swears that he tried to stop you.

01:32:22.929 --> 01:32:27.429
- He was scared that you'd shoot him, too.
- He said you did it. All of it.

01:32:28.728 --> 01:32:31.928
Sure. Now you'd like me to say he did it.

01:32:33.028 --> 01:32:35.328
He's no killer, and he knows it.

01:32:35.928 --> 01:32:38.928
That's why he picked you.
He needed a trigger.

01:32:39.128 --> 01:32:43.027
You had nothing to lose.
You'd already killed a man, in Vegas.

01:32:44.227 --> 01:32:46.927
Beat him to death with a bicycle chain.

01:32:56.227 --> 01:32:59.727
Tough boy. Real brass boy.

01:33:02.127 --> 01:33:04.127
I knew if we got caught...

01:33:04.827 --> 01:33:08.627
...if he dropped his guts,
he'd tell about that guy in Vegas.

01:33:10.727 --> 01:33:12.627
I never killed anybody.

01:33:14.826 --> 01:33:16.626
Not before that night.

01:33:19.226 --> 01:33:21.026
'Cause that night...

01:33:29.726 --> 01:33:31.226
...I think...

01:33:35.026 --> 01:33:37.826
<i>No, I want to remember it the way it was.</i>

01:33:41.626 --> 01:33:44.826
<i>We got there around midnight.</i>

01:33:47.126 --> 01:33:48.426
This is it.

01:33:52.926 --> 01:33:54.926
Let's pull outta here.

01:33:54.926 --> 01:33:57.926
Now, before it's too late.

01:34:05.824 --> 01:34:09.324
If you're gonna do it,
you'll have to do it alone.

01:34:11.824 --> 01:34:14.324
You don't think I got the guts
to do it alone.

01:34:15.024 --> 01:34:18.324
Okay. I'll show you
who's wearing the pants.

01:34:20.624 --> 01:34:24.424
How'd you kill that guy in Vegas, anyhow?
Love him to death?

01:34:26.324 --> 01:34:28.424
Korean War hero.

01:34:28.924 --> 01:34:30.724
Christ!

01:34:43.224 --> 01:34:45.223
<i>Why"d I go along with it?</i>

01:34:46.123 --> 01:34:48.023
<i>When it first began...</i>

01:34:50.223 --> 01:34:52.923
<i>Who knows when anything really begins?</i>

01:34:54.123 --> 01:34:57.723
<i>When Dick first told me the plan
it didn"t even seem real.</i>

01:34:58.923 --> 01:35:02.423
<i>Then, the closer we got,
the more real it became.</i>

01:35:03.723 --> 01:35:08.723
<i>Like the crazy stunt had a life of its own
and nothing could stop it.</i>

01:35:10.323 --> 01:35:12.323
<i>Like I was reading a story...</i>

01:35:12.423 --> 01:35:14.923
<i>... and I had to know
what was gonna happen.</i>

01:35:15.423 --> 01:35:16.923
<i>How it would end.</i>

01:35:56.921 --> 01:35:57.921
Wait.

01:36:06.621 --> 01:36:09.421
If we find the safe,
do you know how to open it?

01:36:10.721 --> 01:36:12.821
I know somebody that knows.

01:36:38.720 --> 01:36:40.820
Honey? Is that you, honey?

01:36:41.320 --> 01:36:42.720
Who is it?

01:36:43.220 --> 01:36:45.120
- Come with us. Now!
- What?

01:36:45.220 --> 01:36:46.220
Come with us.

01:36:56.420 --> 01:36:57.920
In the office.

01:37:09.019 --> 01:37:10.019
Now, sir.

01:37:10.919 --> 01:37:12.719
Where do you keep that safe?

01:37:13.219 --> 01:37:16.419
What safe? I don't have any safe.

01:37:17.219 --> 01:37:19.719
Don't lie to me, you son of a bitch.

01:37:20.219 --> 01:37:24.419
I know you got a safe.
Right here. In this office.

01:37:25.219 --> 01:37:27.719
I'm sorry, but there isn't any safe.

01:37:27.919 --> 01:37:29.819
There never was a safe.

01:37:32.319 --> 01:37:33.919
Any other phones?

01:37:35.219 --> 01:37:37.019
One. In the kitchen.

01:37:42.719 --> 01:37:44.519
Unlock this cabinet.

01:37:44.619 --> 01:37:46.219
It's not locked.

01:37:56.318 --> 01:37:57.718
Where is it?

01:38:14.817 --> 01:38:16.417
Come on, move it.

01:38:20.917 --> 01:38:23.617
All right, now. The money, dig it up.

01:38:33.017 --> 01:38:35.816
Thirty-one lousy dollars.

01:38:37.816 --> 01:38:39.516
A rich man like you.

01:38:40.916 --> 01:38:42.916
You gotta have more money than this.

01:38:43.116 --> 01:38:45.716
Not in cash. I can write you a check.

01:38:47.916 --> 01:38:48.916
A check?

01:38:49.216 --> 01:38:51.816
- What kind of...
- Don't do that!

01:38:51.916 --> 01:38:54.116
- There's somebody awake upstairs.
- My family.

01:38:54.216 --> 01:38:56.116
The only people upstairs...

01:38:56.516 --> 01:38:59.616
...are my wife, my son and daughter.

01:38:59.816 --> 01:39:02.416
Your wife, she got any money?

01:39:02.616 --> 01:39:06.716
- Please, she's not well.
- Sure. Sure, pops.

01:39:07.916 --> 01:39:12.216
- Upstairs.
- My glasses. I can't see without them.

01:39:19.414 --> 01:39:20.814
Upstairs, upstairs.

01:39:28.914 --> 01:39:31.314
Why do you boys want to do this?

01:39:31.414 --> 01:39:32.914
I never harmed you.

01:39:33.914 --> 01:39:38.214
- I never saw you before.
- Shut up. We'll tell you when to talk.

01:39:45.414 --> 01:39:48.114
It's all right, sweetheart, don't be afraid.

01:39:48.214 --> 01:39:50.814
These men, they just want some money.

01:39:52.014 --> 01:39:54.214
They believe we have money
hidden in a safe.

01:39:54.314 --> 01:39:57.814
- I told them we didn't, but they don't...
- Didn't I tell you to shut up?

01:39:57.914 --> 01:40:00.814
He's telling you God's truth.
There isn't any safe.

01:40:00.914 --> 01:40:05.313
I know goddamn well you got a safe.
And you better tell him to find it fast!

01:40:11.813 --> 01:40:15.513
Floyd Wells lied to you.
There isn't any safe.

01:40:18.713 --> 01:40:20.113
Tie them up.

01:40:21.913 --> 01:40:24.513
Okay, lady. In the bathroom.

01:40:33.513 --> 01:40:35.613
Please, don't hurt anybody.

01:40:36.213 --> 01:40:39.512
They don't mean to hurt anyone.
Isn't that right?

01:40:45.312 --> 01:40:48.812
All they want is some money.
And then they'll go away.

01:40:52.111 --> 01:40:54.911
Please, don't hurt the children.

01:40:58.411 --> 01:41:01.311
Good grief! What is this?
Some kind of joke?

01:41:05.611 --> 01:41:08.711
Make one move, holler once...

01:41:09.211 --> 01:41:11.511
...and we'll cut their throats.

01:41:12.411 --> 01:41:15.211
All right. You two, downstairs.

01:41:41.710 --> 01:41:43.210
Dick! In here.

01:41:50.710 --> 01:41:52.410
You. Over there.

01:42:22.309 --> 01:42:24.809
What's this? A casket?

01:42:25.509 --> 01:42:26.809
Hope chest.

01:42:27.209 --> 01:42:29.309
It's a wedding present for my sister.

01:42:31.509 --> 01:42:33.509
Not her. She's too young.

01:42:34.609 --> 01:42:36.809
They're never too young, kid.

01:42:43.109 --> 01:42:44.309
Pops!

01:42:47.209 --> 01:42:50.109
You better pray I find that safe.

01:43:01.809 --> 01:43:03.009
Kenyon?

01:43:05.709 --> 01:43:06.709
Dad?

01:43:27.907 --> 01:43:29.207
You're cold?

01:43:29.607 --> 01:43:30.607
Yes.

01:44:01.206 --> 01:44:03.706
If all you want is money, then why?

01:44:06.306 --> 01:44:09.506
If you do that to my wife she'll panic.

01:44:47.104 --> 01:44:50.104
My mother, please be careful. Please.

01:45:17.104 --> 01:45:20.204
That other man,
I'm afraid he'll hurt someone.

01:45:21.104 --> 01:45:23.704
Please, he can have money, anything...

01:45:24.304 --> 01:45:28.103
...but, please,
don't let him hurt my little girl.

01:45:31.203 --> 01:45:32.503
Don't...

01:45:36.103 --> 01:45:37.803
You ever had a man?

01:45:38.203 --> 01:45:39.803
Please, don't.

01:45:47.103 --> 01:45:48.903
What's eating at you?

01:45:49.303 --> 01:45:51.103
You find the safe?

01:45:52.003 --> 01:45:53.603
Later.

01:45:54.103 --> 01:45:56.803
- First I'm gonna bust that little girl.
- No.

01:45:57.503 --> 01:46:00.502
What do you care? You can bust her, too.

01:46:01.502 --> 01:46:02.502
No.

01:46:04.602 --> 01:46:05.702
Okay, honey.

01:46:10.002 --> 01:46:11.801
Get the kid's radio.

01:46:13.401 --> 01:46:15.301
And then go downstairs.

01:46:28.701 --> 01:46:32.401
I despise people
who can't control themselves.

01:46:43.601 --> 01:46:45.201
You go to school?

01:46:46.301 --> 01:46:47.601
The university...

01:46:47.601 --> 01:46:50.601
...next year. To study music and art.

01:46:53.101 --> 01:46:54.801
I play the guitar.

01:46:55.801 --> 01:46:57.300
Draw some, too.

01:47:00.000 --> 01:47:02.000
Only got as far as the third grade.

01:47:06.000 --> 01:47:07.600
You like horses?

01:47:09.400 --> 01:47:10.400
Yes.

01:47:12.700 --> 01:47:14.100
My mother...

01:47:15.800 --> 01:47:19.700
...was a champion rider. In the rodeo.

01:47:22.400 --> 01:47:24.100
And my father...

01:47:31.400 --> 01:47:32.800
My father...

01:48:04.399 --> 01:48:05.699
What's the matter?

01:48:06.099 --> 01:48:10.199
Us. We're the matter. We're ridiculous.

01:48:11.799 --> 01:48:14.299
You tapping the walls
for a safe that isn't there.

01:48:14.399 --> 01:48:17.399
Tapping like some nutty woodpecker.

01:48:19.199 --> 01:48:20.399
And me.

01:48:21.599 --> 01:48:23.299
Crawling around the floor...

01:48:23.499 --> 01:48:25.499
...with my legs on fire.

01:48:28.898 --> 01:48:33.198
And all to steal a kid's silver dollar.

01:48:37.598 --> 01:48:38.997
Ridiculous!

01:48:40.397 --> 01:48:41.597
This is stupid!

01:48:50.097 --> 01:48:53.097
What are you sore about? We got no beef.

01:48:53.197 --> 01:48:54.997
It's us against them.

01:48:56.497 --> 01:48:58.197
This is between us.

01:48:59.197 --> 01:49:00.997
It's got nothing to do with them.

01:49:05.297 --> 01:49:07.797
Look at me, boy! Take a good look!

01:49:08.397 --> 01:49:11.497
I'm the last living thing
you're ever gonna see.

01:50:36.594 --> 01:50:38.994
Don't. Please, don't.

01:51:02.993 --> 01:51:04.593
It doesn't make sense.

01:51:06.193 --> 01:51:07.593
I mean what happened.

01:51:08.593 --> 01:51:09.593
Or why.

01:51:11.693 --> 01:51:14.093
It had nothing to do with the Clutters.

01:51:14.793 --> 01:51:17.993
They never hurt me,
they just happened to be there.

01:51:20.292 --> 01:51:22.892
I thought Mr. Clutter
was a very nice gentleman.

01:51:26.492 --> 01:51:29.392
I thought so right up until the time
I cut his throat.

01:52:38.590 --> 01:52:40.990
Mercy for them.

01:52:42.390 --> 01:52:43.290
The killers.

01:52:45.090 --> 01:52:48.290
How fortunate
that their admirable attorneys...

01:52:49.390 --> 01:52:53.190
...were not present at the Clutter home
that fateful evening.

01:52:53.390 --> 01:52:56.190
How fortunate for them
that they were not there...

01:52:56.290 --> 01:52:59.890
...to plead mercy for the doomed family...

01:53:00.690 --> 01:53:02.689
...because otherwise...

01:53:02.989 --> 01:53:05.289
...we would have found their corpses, too.

01:53:07.089 --> 01:53:09.589
If you allow them life imprisonment...

01:53:10.989 --> 01:53:14.289
...they will be eligible for parole
in seven years.

01:53:15.089 --> 01:53:17.789
That is the law.

01:53:20.189 --> 01:53:21.589
Gentlemen...

01:53:22.189 --> 01:53:24.189
...four of your neighbors...

01:53:24.589 --> 01:53:27.989
...were slaughtered like hogs in a pen...

01:53:28.589 --> 01:53:29.989
...by them.

01:53:32.489 --> 01:53:35.589
They did not strike in the heat of passion...

01:53:36.189 --> 01:53:37.589
...but for money.

01:53:38.689 --> 01:53:40.789
They did not kill in vengeance.

01:53:41.389 --> 01:53:43.589
They planned it for money.

01:53:44.689 --> 01:53:46.189
And how cheaply...

01:53:46.689 --> 01:53:48.688
...those lives were bought.

01:53:50.788 --> 01:53:51.988
$40.

01:53:53.488 --> 01:53:55.388
$10 a life.

01:53:56.988 --> 01:53:59.487
They drove 400 miles to come here...

01:54:00.687 --> 01:54:03.187
...they brought their weapons with them.

01:54:03.287 --> 01:54:06.987
This shotgun, this dagger.

01:54:07.187 --> 01:54:10.687
This is the rope
that they hogtied their victims with.

01:54:15.887 --> 01:54:18.187
This is the blood they spilled.

01:54:22.887 --> 01:54:24.487
Herb Clutter's.

01:54:26.687 --> 01:54:29.887
They who had no pity, now ask for yours.

01:54:30.787 --> 01:54:34.186
They who had no mercy,
now ask for yours.

01:54:35.086 --> 01:54:38.486
They who had no tears, now ask for yours.

01:54:39.086 --> 01:54:42.786
If you have tears to shed,
weep not for them...

01:54:44.086 --> 01:54:46.086
...weep for their victims.

01:54:46.886 --> 01:54:51.886
From the way the Holy Bible
was quoted here today...

01:54:52.286 --> 01:54:56.886
...you might think the word of God
was written only to protect the killers.

01:54:57.286 --> 01:54:59.786
But they didn't read you this:

01:55:00.986 --> 01:55:02.886
Exodus 20...

01:55:03.486 --> 01:55:05.886
...verse 13:

01:55:06.386 --> 01:55:08.986
"Thou shalt not kill."

01:55:10.486 --> 01:55:11.486
Or this...

01:55:12.186 --> 01:55:15.486
...Genesis 9, verse 12:

01:55:16.486 --> 01:55:19.484
"Who so shedeth man's blood...

01:55:20.184 --> 01:55:24.384
"...by man shall his blood be shed."

01:55:34.684 --> 01:55:37.484
<i>It took four hours to pick the jury.</i>

01:55:38.784 --> 01:55:41.684
<i>It took the state three days
to present its case.</i>

01:55:44.184 --> 01:55:46.784
<i>It took the defense one hour and a half.</i>

01:55:49.284 --> 01:55:51.184
<i>It took the jury...</i>

01:55:51.184 --> 01:55:53.684
<i>... 40 minutes to bring in the verdict.</i>

01:55:59.984 --> 01:56:01.784
<i>They had to be crazy.</i>

01:56:02.784 --> 01:56:06.483
<i>No. Maybe stupid, but perfectly sane.</i>

01:56:08.183 --> 01:56:10.183
<i>How can a perfectly sane man...</i>

01:56:11.583 --> 01:56:13.883
<i>... commit an absolutely crazy act?</i>

01:56:40.482 --> 01:56:43.082
<i>Calling all stations, Officer Linhard...</i>

01:56:43.382 --> 01:56:44.982
<i>... Officer Brackin.</i>

01:56:45.182 --> 01:56:47.382
<i>Please come to the desk sergeant"s office.</i>

01:56:47.882 --> 01:56:50.181
<i>Calling all stations, Officer C. Wright.</i>

01:56:51.981 --> 01:56:53.781
<i>Please call the desk sergeant.</i>

01:56:57.881 --> 01:57:00.881
- What happens now?
- They wait to die.

01:57:02.981 --> 01:57:06.081
I wonder how many others
are waiting in other prisons?

01:57:06.281 --> 01:57:07.681
About 200.

01:57:16.481 --> 01:57:19.781
<i>Perry and Dick began their waiting
in the "S and l" building...</i>

01:57:20.281 --> 01:57:22.781
<i>... Security and Isolation.</i>

01:57:25.481 --> 01:57:28.181
<i>The second floor is death row.</i>

01:57:37.980 --> 01:57:41.280
<i>Through the window
they can see the baseball field.</i>

01:57:43.980 --> 01:57:46.580
<i>Beyond the outfield, over the wall...</i>

01:57:46.980 --> 01:57:50.180
<i>... is an old warehouse with a tin roof.</i>

01:57:54.180 --> 01:57:55.880
This warehouse got a name?

01:57:57.380 --> 01:58:00.180
In this prison, it's called "The Corner."

01:58:00.380 --> 01:58:04.380
On hanging day, the men say,
"He's gone to 'The Corner'."

01:58:05.880 --> 01:58:08.480
Perry and Dick have a date at "The Corner."

01:58:08.680 --> 01:58:13.580
One minute after midnight.
May, Friday 13.

01:58:20.480 --> 01:58:23.479
<i>According to an expert
in forensic medicine...</i>

01:58:23.979 --> 01:58:26.279
<i>... neither one of them
would have done it alone.</i>

01:58:26.779 --> 01:58:29.679
<i>But together,
they made a third personality.</i>

01:58:30.479 --> 01:58:32.079
<i>That"s the one that did it.</i>

01:58:37.479 --> 01:58:38.879
Hey, Andy!

01:58:40.179 --> 01:58:43.679
Does it tell anywhere in them books
what happens when you make the drop?

01:58:45.279 --> 01:58:47.079
Well, your neck breaks...

01:58:48.979 --> 01:58:51.079
...and you crap your pants.

01:58:52.779 --> 01:58:56.379
The trouble with you, Andy,
you got no respect for human life...

01:58:56.479 --> 01:58:58.279
...not even your own.

01:59:19.177 --> 01:59:23.477
<i>Doomsday, Friday 13, came and went...</i>

01:59:24.577 --> 01:59:26.577
<i>... but no one went to "The Corner."</i>

01:59:28.477 --> 01:59:31.077
<i>Perry and Dick appealed. Routine.</i>

01:59:32.977 --> 01:59:36.377
<i>They were granted a stay of execution.
Routine.</i>

01:59:37.577 --> 01:59:42.777
<i>The legal machinery in capital cases
usually runs a year or more. Routine.</i>

01:59:43.877 --> 01:59:46.477
<i>Death row has its own routine.</i>

01:59:48.677 --> 01:59:51.677
<i>Shower. One man at a time, once a week.</i>

01:59:52.676 --> 01:59:54.476
<i>Shave, twice a week.</i>

01:59:55.076 --> 01:59:57.576
<i>The guard locks the safety razor.</i>

01:59:58.476 --> 01:59:59.876
<i>Safety first.</i>

02:00:00.976 --> 02:00:04.876
<i>No radios, no movies, no TV.</i>

02:00:06.276 --> 02:00:08.976
<i>No cards, no games, no exercise.</i>

02:00:10.176 --> 02:00:13.276
<i>No mirrors, no bottles, no glasses.</i>

02:00:14.176 --> 02:00:15.976
<i>No knives, no forks.</i>

02:00:16.876 --> 02:00:18.676
<i>No suicide allowed.</i>

02:00:19.176 --> 02:00:21.076
<i>They could eat, sleep...</i>

02:00:21.676 --> 02:00:24.676
<i>... write, read, think, dream.</i>

02:00:25.276 --> 02:00:27.676
<i>They could pray, if so inclined.</i>

02:00:27.876 --> 02:00:30.576
<i>But mostly, they just waited.</i>

02:00:32.776 --> 02:00:36.676
The guy in the next cell, Andy.
He's been waiting two years.

02:00:37.376 --> 02:00:40.874
Newspapers call him
"The nicest boy in Kansas."

02:00:41.774 --> 02:00:44.274
One night he killed his sister.

02:00:45.274 --> 02:00:49.974
Then he shot his mother six times
and his father seventeen times.

02:00:51.474 --> 02:00:53.174
Andy's a nut, but I like him.

02:00:53.974 --> 02:00:56.774
Hey, Andy. Say hello to Mr. Jensen.

02:00:57.374 --> 02:00:59.374
He's writing the story of my life.

02:01:00.574 --> 02:01:01.674
Why?

02:01:03.874 --> 02:01:05.774
I told you he was a nut.

02:01:05.874 --> 02:01:08.974
Ronnie, Jim, meet Mr. Jensen.

02:01:10.774 --> 02:01:13.874
They knocked off seven. Strangers.

02:01:14.874 --> 02:01:17.474
Ronnie said they was better off dead.

02:01:20.474 --> 02:01:23.174
What about Perry? Don't you get along?

02:01:25.273 --> 02:01:27.973
Nobody can get along with him.

02:01:28.873 --> 02:01:31.673
There's five guys waiting here
for the big swing.

02:01:32.373 --> 02:01:36.273
Little Perry's the only one yapping
against capital punishment.

02:01:37.073 --> 02:01:39.273
Don't tell me you're for it?

02:01:40.073 --> 02:01:43.273
Hell, hanging's only getting revenge.

02:01:44.373 --> 02:01:46.473
What's wrong with revenge?

02:01:47.473 --> 02:01:49.973
I've been revenging myself all my life.

02:01:51.673 --> 02:01:54.773
Sure. I'm for hanging.

02:01:56.473 --> 02:01:59.372
Just so long as I'm not the one
being hanged.

02:02:01.972 --> 02:02:02.972
See you.

02:02:03.472 --> 02:02:05.472
Thanks for the magazines.

02:02:07.072 --> 02:02:09.871
Jim, you think that looks like Willie Jay?

02:02:10.471 --> 02:02:12.471
The way you see him, yes.

02:02:14.871 --> 02:02:18.671
That day at the bus station,
when I phoned you.

02:02:19.971 --> 02:02:23.871
If Willie Jay and I had connected,
none of this would of happened.

02:02:23.971 --> 02:02:28.371
- Maybe, if you hadn't come back to Kansas.
- Maybe!

02:02:28.871 --> 02:02:31.771
If they'd had a head-doctor here
during my first stretch...

02:02:31.771 --> 02:02:34.471
...he would've known
I had a bomb ticking inside of me.

02:02:34.571 --> 02:02:36.871
He would've known
I wasn't ready for parole.

02:02:36.971 --> 02:02:38.371
- You knew.
- Yeah.

02:02:38.471 --> 02:02:39.971
Why didn't you tell me?

02:02:42.471 --> 02:02:45.971
Then I wouldn't have gotten my parole,
would I, Reverend?

02:02:50.571 --> 02:02:53.771
<i>A few minutes after midnight,
in November...</i>

02:02:55.370 --> 02:02:57.670
<i>... one of them went to "The Corner."</i>

02:02:58.770 --> 02:03:03.570
<i>The others watched him cross the ball field
on his way to the gallows.</i>

02:03:04.870 --> 02:03:06.270
<i>It was Andy.</i>

02:03:06.970 --> 02:03:09.070
<i>"The nicest boy in Kansas."</i>

02:03:16.570 --> 02:03:18.670
<i>They heard the trapdoor go.</i>

02:03:19.870 --> 02:03:24.070
<i>The kept watching and waiting
for 19 minutes...</i>

02:03:24.570 --> 02:03:26.770
<i>... till Andy"s heart stopped beating.</i>

02:03:27.870 --> 02:03:30.270
<i>For Andy, the waiting was over.</i>

02:03:33.070 --> 02:03:35.470
<i>Perry and Dick waited five years.</i>

02:03:36.170 --> 02:03:40.070
<i>Three times their case went
to the United States Supreme Court.</i>

02:04:09.869 --> 02:04:12.769
My God! That harness!

02:04:14.069 --> 02:04:18.569
Richard, this is a warrant from
the Supreme Court of the State of Kansas.

02:04:19.169 --> 02:04:21.169
"Whereas, it was by this court ordered...

02:04:21.269 --> 02:04:25.669
"...that execution of the sentence of death
by hanging of Richard Eugene Hickock...

02:04:25.769 --> 02:04:28.568
"...imposed by the District Court
of Finney County, Kansas...

02:04:28.868 --> 02:04:32.368
"...be carried out on Wednesday,
April 14, 1965.

02:04:32.468 --> 02:04:35.268
"Commanding the warden
of the Kansas State Penitentiary...

02:04:35.368 --> 02:04:37.468
"...to carry the sentence into execution."

02:04:37.568 --> 02:04:39.067
Where's Smith?

02:04:41.067 --> 02:04:43.467
"Yea, let none that wait for thee
be ashamed.

02:04:43.567 --> 02:04:46.767
"Let them be ashamed
which transgress without cause.

02:04:47.067 --> 02:04:50.067
"Show me thy ways, O Lord,
teach me thy paths.

02:04:50.367 --> 02:04:53.267
"Lead me in thy truth, and teach me,
for thou art the God..."

02:04:58.967 --> 02:05:00.767
I gotta go to the toilet.

02:05:00.867 --> 02:05:04.267
We can't remove the harness.
There might not be time.

02:05:05.767 --> 02:05:06.967
Please.

02:05:07.067 --> 02:05:09.067
Try to control yourself.

02:05:10.167 --> 02:05:11.667
But that's it.

02:05:12.666 --> 02:05:16.466
When you hit the end of the rope
your muscles lose control.

02:05:22.566 --> 02:05:24.566
I'm afraid I'll mess myself.

02:05:24.566 --> 02:05:27.666
It's nothing to be ashamed of.
They all do it.

02:05:28.466 --> 02:05:30.466
For God's sake, man!

02:05:38.066 --> 02:05:42.266
"This is to command you, the warden
of the Kansas State Penitentiary...

02:05:42.366 --> 02:05:45.866
"...that on Wednesday, April 14, 1965...

02:05:46.266 --> 02:05:50.966
"...between the hours of 12:01 a.m.
And 2:00 a. M..."

02:05:51.966 --> 02:05:53.666
Is he the...

02:05:55.466 --> 02:05:57.866
How much does he get paid to hang them?

02:05:57.866 --> 02:05:59.964
$300 a man.

02:06:01.764 --> 02:06:03.364
Has he got a name?

02:06:04.264 --> 02:06:05.864
"We, the people."

02:06:07.464 --> 02:06:09.564
"...for the State of Kansas."

02:06:09.664 --> 02:06:11.664
Anything you want to say?

02:06:13.564 --> 02:06:17.764
Just that I hold no hard feelings.

02:06:19.664 --> 02:06:23.764
You're sending me to a better world
than this ever was.

02:06:28.964 --> 02:06:30.464
Nice to see you.

02:06:49.063 --> 02:06:51.563
Jim, Thoreau...

02:06:52.763 --> 02:06:54.663
...on man and nature.

02:06:54.863 --> 02:06:57.663
It's yours if you want it.

02:07:00.363 --> 02:07:01.663
Dick gone?

02:07:03.063 --> 02:07:05.163
Is his heart still beating?

02:07:09.663 --> 02:07:12.263
- What time is it?
- Take it easy, kid.

02:07:16.463 --> 02:07:19.162
Would you like me to write your father?

02:07:21.662 --> 02:07:24.362
I could send him one of your paintings.

02:07:24.462 --> 02:07:26.562
Or maybe your Bronze Star.

02:07:31.361 --> 02:07:33.361
Send him my treasure maps.

02:07:34.761 --> 02:07:36.761
Maybe now he'll get lucky.

02:07:39.361 --> 02:07:41.061
The Lone Wolf.

02:07:44.061 --> 02:07:48.861
You know, there was a time once
when we almost had it made.

02:07:50.161 --> 02:07:51.861
Just the two of us.

02:07:53.461 --> 02:07:58.161
He was in a fever about some new project
up in Alaska.

02:07:59.061 --> 02:08:01.161
A hunting lodge for tourists.

02:08:01.261 --> 02:08:05.561
It was gonna make us a fortune
better than a gold mine.

02:08:07.461 --> 02:08:11.361
But most of all, it was gonna be something
we never had before:

02:08:12.761 --> 02:08:14.261
A real home.

02:08:15.560 --> 02:08:17.160
We got it built, too.

02:08:17.360 --> 02:08:19.960
Just him and me, side by side.

02:08:20.560 --> 02:08:24.860
The day the roof was finished,
he danced all over it.

02:08:26.460 --> 02:08:28.960
I never was so happy in all my life.

02:08:30.360 --> 02:08:32.860
It was a beautiful home.

02:08:38.560 --> 02:08:40.960
But no tourists ever came.

02:08:42.060 --> 02:08:43.960
Nobody.

02:08:45.960 --> 02:08:47.560
We just lived there...

02:08:47.860 --> 02:08:52.260
...all alone in that big, empty failure...

02:08:56.460 --> 02:08:59.160
...till he couldn't stand the sight of me.

02:09:02.759 --> 02:09:04.559
I think it happened...

02:09:06.859 --> 02:09:08.859
I was eating a biscuit.

02:09:10.259 --> 02:09:13.759
He started yelling what a greedy,
selfish bastard I was.

02:09:14.859 --> 02:09:17.159
Yelling and yelling till I grabbed his throat.

02:09:17.259 --> 02:09:19.159
I couldn't stop myself.

02:09:19.659 --> 02:09:21.759
He tore loose and got a gun.

02:09:23.459 --> 02:09:25.959
He said, "Look at me, boy!

02:09:27.759 --> 02:09:32.259
"Take a good look 'cause
I'm the last living thing you're gonna see."

02:09:36.159 --> 02:09:38.159
And he pulled the trigger.

02:09:41.059 --> 02:09:43.059
But the gun wasn't loaded.

02:09:45.159 --> 02:09:46.758
He began to cry.

02:09:49.658 --> 02:09:51.358
Bawled like a kid.

02:09:53.658 --> 02:09:55.258
I went for a long walk.

02:09:57.158 --> 02:09:59.357
When I got back, the place was dark.

02:10:00.457 --> 02:10:02.257
The door was locked.

02:10:03.657 --> 02:10:06.957
All my stuff was piled outside
in the snow...

02:10:07.457 --> 02:10:09.157
...where he threw it.

02:10:09.657 --> 02:10:12.657
I walked away and never looked back.

02:10:15.757 --> 02:10:19.157
I guess the only thing I'm gonna miss
in this world...

02:10:20.657 --> 02:10:22.557
...is that poor old man...

02:10:24.257 --> 02:10:27.157
...and his hopeless dreams.

02:10:31.357 --> 02:10:34.356
I'm glad you don't hate
your father anymore.

02:10:35.856 --> 02:10:37.156
But I do.

02:10:39.956 --> 02:10:41.256
I hate him.

02:10:43.956 --> 02:10:45.556
And I love him.

02:11:12.656 --> 02:11:14.756
- Coming?
- What for?

02:11:14.956 --> 02:11:17.056
What does it add up to, anyway?

02:11:17.556 --> 02:11:20.854
Well, four innocent
and two guilty people murdered.

02:11:20.854 --> 02:11:22.754
Three families broken.

02:11:23.254 --> 02:11:25.254
Newspapers have sold more papers.

02:11:25.254 --> 02:11:27.654
Politicians will make more speeches.

02:11:28.054 --> 02:11:30.954
Police and parole boards
will get more blame.

02:11:32.054 --> 02:11:33.754
More laws will be passed.

02:11:33.954 --> 02:11:36.354
Everybody will pass the buck.

02:11:36.754 --> 02:11:40.454
And then, next month, next year...

02:11:41.554 --> 02:11:43.554
...the same thing will happen again.

02:11:44.154 --> 02:11:46.754
Well, maybe this will help to stop it.

02:11:47.454 --> 02:11:48.754
Never has.

02:12:04.753 --> 02:12:09.553
This is a warrant from the Supreme Court
of the State of Kansas.

02:12:11.353 --> 02:12:15.453
"It was by the court ordered that execution
of the sentence of death by hanging...

02:12:15.553 --> 02:12:17.153
"...of Perry Edward Smith...

02:12:17.153 --> 02:12:20.153
"...imposed by the District Court
of Finney County, Kansas...

02:12:20.253 --> 02:12:23.753
"...be carried out on Wednesday,
April 14, 1965."

02:12:27.253 --> 02:12:29.253
Anything you want to say?

02:12:36.853 --> 02:12:38.452
I think maybe...

02:12:41.452 --> 02:12:43.952
...I'd like to apologize.

02:12:46.052 --> 02:12:47.452
But who to?

02:13:10.151 --> 02:13:13.151
"The Lord is my shepherd,
I shall not want...

02:13:13.351 --> 02:13:16.151
"...he maketh me to lie down
in green pastures.

02:13:16.351 --> 02:13:18.951
"He leadeth me beside the still waters...

02:13:19.051 --> 02:13:20.851
"...he restoreth my soul.

02:13:21.451 --> 02:13:25.151
"He leadeth me in the paths
of righteousness for his name's sake.

02:13:25.751 --> 02:13:29.651
"Yea, though I walk through the valley
of the shadow of death...

02:13:29.851 --> 02:13:31.851
"...I will fear no evil...

02:13:32.051 --> 02:13:33.751
"...for thou art with me...

02:13:33.851 --> 02:13:36.550
"...thy rod and thy staff, they comfort me.

02:13:37.350 --> 02:13:41.050
"Thou preparest a table before me
in the presence of mine enemies...

02:13:41.150 --> 02:13:43.550
"...thou anointest my head with oil..."

02:13:44.250 --> 02:13:46.250
Is God in this place, too?

02:13:49.450 --> 02:13:51.250
"...my cup runneth over.

02:13:52.550 --> 02:13:56.650
"Surely goodness and mercy
will follow me all the days of my life...

02:13:57.550 --> 02:14:00.850
"...and I will dwell
in the house of the Lord forever."

